cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with RF sensing networks, which are a type of wireless sensor network (WSN) used for localization and tracking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes adapting background subtraction methods from computer vision, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the second most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for tasks such as tracking, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses experimental data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
